abstract: JPMorgan’s profit on mortages fell 14 percent last quarter, while at Wells mortgage originations dropped.
snippet: JPMorgan’s profit on mortages fell 14 percent last quarter, while at Wells mortgage originations dropped.
lead_paragraph: Even as two of the nation’s largest banks reported record profits on Friday, beneath the rosy earnings were signs that a sharp uptick in interest rates could spell trouble ahead for Wall Street and the broader housing market.

headline.main: JPMorgan and Wells Fargo Feel First Chill of Rising Interest Rates
headline.print_headline: JPMorgan and Wells Fargo Feel First Chill of Rising Interest Rates

byline.original: By Jessica Silver-Greenberg and Ben Protess

abstract: Wells Fargo, the nation’s largest home lender, overcame a slowdown in the mortgage market to report record net income of $5.5 billion, or 98 cents a share.
snippet: Wells Fargo, the nation’s largest home lender, overcame a slowdown in the mortgage market to report record net income of $5.5 billion, or 98 cents a share.
lead_paragraph: Wells Fargo, the nation’s largest home lender, posted a 19 percent increase in second-quarter profit on Friday as it overcame a drop-off in the mortgage market on its way to record earnings.
